05/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Serbia-Montenegro Parliament unanimously adopted a new resolution on Kosovo Thursday (4 September). 
The document builds on previous declarations, adding that Pristina and Belgrade must work to start dialogue as soon as possible. 
The essence of the declaration is that the UN Security Council resolution on Kosovo must be implemented, setting standards to be followed. 
(B92, BBC, Beta, FoNet, Tanjug - 04/09/03)
